line_1: She must not soil her dainty foot,
An Orange-wench trod on his Foot;
line_2: And screaming, "Will you have some Fruit?"

line_1: Nay, — now I cannot stir my Foot:
line_2: It feels as if 'twere taking Root.

line_1: Since the dear hour that brought me to thy foot,
line_2: And cut up all my follies by the root,

line_1: In honour's field advancing his firm foot,
line_2: Who, with a courage of unshaken root,

line_1: You may know by the Hand, it had no Cloven Foot.
line_2: And tho' some Malicious Young Spirit did do't,

line_1: How they'd not stir a single foot,
line_2: 'Till crook or cur had set 'em to't.
